VM Manager
==========

This manages QEMU VMs via a REST API, which is a surprisingly
hard to find feature in pre-build solutions.

Build
-----

```
$ go install .
```

Run Prod
--------

```
$ vm-manager -p <port>
```

e.g.

```
$ vm-manager -p 1701
```

Run Dev
-------

```
$ cd bootdev
$ go build .
$ cd ..
$ go run .
```

FOR DEVELOPERS - API
--------------------

- GET  /vm           : returns JSON blob of started VMs
- GET  /vm/:id       : returns relevant info for vm id
- POST /vm/start/:id : starts vm id
- POST /vm/kill/:id  : stops vm id with `kill -9`

